        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 6:28AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 628 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pittsboro, or 21 miles west of Houston, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Houston, Bruce, Calhoun City, Vardaman, Derma, Pittsboro, Slate
Springs, Sabougla, Pyland, Trebloc, Houlka, New Houlka, Algoma, Big
Creek, Woodland, Robbs, Thorn, Reid, Loyd, and Ellard.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
